The paper deals with deep learning and domain adaptation, which are both topics commonly found in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of residual networks is also a key aspect of the paper, which is a popular technique in deep learning research and is often found in papers related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the approach for image classification tasks, which is a common application of multimedia (cs.MM) research.
